entry.title: The Equality Act 2010 (Qualifying Compromise Contract Specified Person) Order 2010
entry.summary: This Order extends the category of person capable of acting as an independent adviser whose advice is necessary to establish a qualifying compromise contract under Part 10 of the Equality Act 2010 (“the Act”) to a Fellow of the Institute of Legal Executives practising in a solicitor’s practice including an incorporated practice recognised by the Law Society under section 9(1) of the Administration of Justice Act 1985.

entry.title: The Addition of Vitamins, Minerals and Other Substances (Amendment) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2010
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Addition of Vitamins, Minerals and Other Substances Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2007 (S.R. 2007 No. 301) to the effect that where those Regulations mention “the EC Regulation”, that reference will be ambulatory to a specified extent. Any such reference will be to Regulation (EC) No. 1925/2006 of the European Parliament and of the Council on the addition of vitamins and minerals and of certain other substances to foods (OJ No. L404, 30.12.2006, p.26) as that Regulation may be amended from time to time by changes made to its Annexes I or II. These Annexes have been previously amended by Commission Regulation (EC) No. 1170/2009 (OJ No. L314, 1.12.2009, p.36).

entry.title: The Equality Act 2010 (Obtaining Information) Order 2010
entry.summary: This Order prescribes forms on which a person who thinks that he or she may have been the subject of a contravention of the Equality Act 2010 (“the Act”), including the breach of an equality clause or rule, (P), may ask questions of a person who he or she thinks was responsible for the contravention or breach (R) and also prescribes forms on which R may reply.

entry.title: The North Western Inshore Fisheries and Conservation Order 2010
entry.summary: This Order makes provision for the establishment of the North Western Inshore Fisheries and Conservation District (article 3) and for the North Western Inshore Fisheries and Conservation Authority (“the Authority”) for that district (article 4).

entry.title: The Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (Amendment) (No.2) (England) Order 2010
entry.summary: The Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) Order 1995 (S.I. 1995/418) (“the GPDO”) grants planning permission for specified development without the need for a planning application. The amendments made to it in this Order apply to England only.

entry.title: The Occupational Pension Schemes (Investment) (Amendment) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2010
entry.summary: These Regulations implement the requirements of Article 18(1)(f) of the European Union Directive 2003/41/EC on the activities and supervision of institutions for occupational retirement provision (O.J. No. L235, 23.9.03, p.10) (“the Directive”) as it applies to investments by an operator of a collective investment scheme and to investments subject to certain transitional protection.

entry.title: The Town and Country Planning (Compensation) (No.3) (England) Regulations 2010
entry.summary: Section 108 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 provides for the payment of compensation in certain cases where planning permission for development granted by a development order or a local development order is withdrawn and where on an application for planning permission for that development, the application is refused or permission is granted subject to conditions.

entry.title: The Tonnage Tax (Training Requirement) (Amendment) Regulations 2010
The Knife Dealer’s Licence (Miscellaneous) (Scotland) Order 2010
entry.summary: This Order makes exceptions to the requirement for a knife dealer’s licence under section 27A of the Civic Government (Scotland) Act 1982 (“the Act”).

entry.title: The Environmental Permitting (England and Wales) (Amendment) (No. 2) Regulations 2010

ukm:Supersedes.dc:title: The Environmental Permitting (England and Wales) (Amendment) (No. 2) Regulations 2009

entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Environmental Permitting (England and Wales) Regulations 2010 (S.I. 2010/675)(“the EP Regulations”). They make certain amendments to the EP Regulations relating to the activities listed in Schedule 1 that require an environmental permit. Regulation 2(1) to (4) amends Part 2 of Schedule 1 to the EP Regulations by making amendments to the regulation of certain activities involving the melting of non-ferrous metals, the manufacture of powder coating materials which do not use lead chromate or triglycidyl isocyanurate and adding the drying of green crops to the list of activities excluded from regulation.

entry.title: The Marine and Coastal Access Act 2009 (Commencement No.4 and Transitional Provisions) Order 2010
entry.summary: Article 3 of this Order brings into force various sections of the Marine and Coastal Access Act 2009 (“the 2009 Act”), which relate to Inshore Fisheries and Conservation Authorities (IFCAs). Article 4 contains transitional provisions.

entry.title: The Eastern Inshore Fisheries and Conservation Order 2010
entry.summary: This Order makes provision for the establishment of the Eastern Inshore Fisheries and Conservation District (article 3) and for the Eastern Inshore Fisheries and Conservation Authority (“the Authority”) for that district (article 4).

entry.title: The Southern Inshore Fisheries and Conservation Order 2010
entry.summary: This Order makes provision for the establishment of the Southern Inshore Fisheries and Conservation District (article 3) and for the Southern Inshore Fisheries and Conservation Authority (“the Authority”) for that district (article 4).

entry.title: The North Eastern Inshore Fisheries and Conservation Order 2010
entry.summary: This Order makes provision for the establishment of the North Eastern Inshore Fisheries and Conservation District (article 3) and for the North Eastern Inshore Fisheries and Conservation Authority (“the Authority”) for that district (article 4).

entry.title: The Electricity (Applications for Licences, Modifications of an Area and Extensions and Restrictions of Licences) Regulations 2010
entry.summary: These Regulations set out the information and other documents that are required to be submitted with applications for generation, transmission, distribution, supply and interconnector licences (and for modifications of an area of transmission licences and extensions, or restrictions of supply and distribution licences) under the Electricity Act 1989, as amended by the Utilities Act 2000 and the Energy Act 2004. They specify the form and manner of such applications. These Regulations also set out the manner in which notices of applications are to be published.

entry.title: The Sussex Inshore Fisheries and Conservation Order 2010
entry.summary: This Order makes provision for the establishment of the Sussex Inshore Fisheries and Conservation District (article 3) and for the Sussex Inshore Fisheries and Conservation Authority (“the Authority”) for that district (article 4).

entry.title: The Cornwall Inshore Fisheries and Conservation Order 2010
entry.summary: This Order makes provision for the establishment of the Cornwall Inshore Fisheries and Conservation District (article 3) and for the Cornwall Inshore Fisheries and Conservation Authority (“the Authority”) for that district (article 4).

entry.title: The Northumberland Inshore Fisheries and Conservation Order 2010
entry.summary: This Order makes provision for the establishment of the Northumberland Inshore Fisheries and Conservation District (article 3) and for the Northumberland Inshore Fisheries and Conservation Authority (“the Authority”) for that district (article 4).

entry.title: The Gas (Applications for Licences and Extensions and Restrictions of Licences) Regulations 2010
entry.summary: These Regulations set out the information, and other documents that are required to be submitted with applications for supplier, shipper, transporter and interconnector licences (and for extensions or restrictions of supplier, shipper and transporter licences) under the Gas Act 1986, as amended by the Utilities Act 2000 and the Energy Act 2004. They specify the form and manner of such applications. These Regulations also set out the manner in which notices of applications are to be published.

entry.title: The Flood and Water Management Act 2010 (Commencement No. 1 and Transitional Provisions) Order 2010

ukm:Subject.Value: FLOOD RISK MANAGEMENT, ENGLAND AND WALES

category.term: FLOOD RISK MANAGEMENT, ENGLAND AND WALES

entry.summary: This Order brings into force provisions of the Flood and Water Management Act 2010 (“the Act”) to provide power for Ministers to make orders and regulations to give effect to the Act. The Order refers to the relevant definitions of “the Minister”.
